value.0: Welcome to the shop, as I like to say. I am Eltoora Sarptyl, and a finer collection of wares you are not apt to find.
Well, hello. Have you exciting news for me, or is this just a routine visit? Either way, I'm pleased to see you again.
Well, far be it from me to keep you from your duties. Visit again when you have need of us. Farewell.
Well, well, well. I do indeed have a task for you. How do you feel about recovering some old tomes for me?
That's fine. Was there something else you needed?
The best way that I can explain their purpose, with brevity, is to compare them to recipe books. These books explain the crafting of magical items.
If you return these books to me, I will of course also offer a suitable reward, not only gold but most notably a powerful tome that can enhance one of your characteristics.
Scattered about the region are the Five Tomes of Ancient Imaskar. I want you to find these tomes, and return them here to me.
If you can do this, then I will reward you far beyond the value of the books. Of that, you can be certain.
The five tomes that I want you to find are the tomes of Resonance, Life, Death, Ice, and Fire.
My scrying has shown that the Tome of Resonance was originally taken far south into the Mere of Dead Men. Perhaps if you go to the swamp, a clue or two will reveal itself.
As for the Tome of Life, I believe it was in the possession of Brother Toras, a member of the Arcane Brotherhood. I had planned to buy it from him, but he died before I had the chance.
I checked around when I heard he was dead, but it wasn't amongst his personal possessions. The only place I haven't searched yet is his tomb; which is in Luskan.

Further scrying reveals that the Tome of Death has followed a long, dark path towards Helm's Hold. If only I could see more, but the region is impervious to my efforts. Perhaps there is something more... malevolent, there.
To the far north towards Icewind Dale, you shall find the Tome of Ice. I know nothing more, for my scrying is blocked by the frigid frost.
Finally, the Tome of Fire has been a tricky one for me to locate. My scrying attempts reveal that it is somewhere in Neverwinter Wood.
Specifically, it would make sense that the tome was within the Charwood. Though I know not why, that realm resists my scrying. If it were anywhere else, I think I could locate it.
That would be most excellent. I eagerly await your return.
Indeed you have. And I shall give you your reward as promised - a magical book that can enhance your abilities once a day merely by reading it's pages. Which ability do you want do hone?
You should, because I'm only willing to part with one. Was there something else I can assist you with?
Of course. But are you certain? I won't swap books if you change your mind.
And you shall have it. I hope this book will serve you well in your adventures.

Well, the Tome of Fire! That will be a nice addition to my collection. Thank you very much, and now for your reward.
Ah, the Tome of Ice. Another fine work to add to my collection. I thank you for this. Here is some gold for your trouble.
Well, what an exquisite book. I've always thought death was such a beautiful, misunderstood thing. This book shall serve as my center piece. Here is your reward, as promised.
Oh, this shall be an exciting tome to page through, I would say. This makes me happy indeed. And for you, some gold.

Well, well, the Tome of Resonance. Though I hoped otherwise, I felt certain I would never see it amongst my collection. You have my admiration, and appreciation. I think you'll find this gold quite suitable.
Yes. Which familiar do you want?
Very well. Anything else I can do for you?
Alright, enjoy your new familiar.
I must be on my way.
I'm looking for work. Do you know of any?
Not interested.
What are these tomes? What do they do?
Good. Tell me more.
I will find these tomes for you.
I have brought you all five Imaskarran Tomes.
I need more time to think about this.

Yes, I'm sure.
